William LITTLES a/k/a Bill Littles, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 25160. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. March 14, 1968. William Littles, pro se. Robert S. Travis, Asst. U. S. Atty., Fort Worth, Tex., for appellee.

Before WISDOM, BELL and DYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

The judgment of the district court denying appellant relief under § 2255 is affirmed.
